  "overview_metadata": {
    "overview_number": 1,
    "overview_title": "The Right Triangle Connection",
    "overview_subtitle": "The Pythagorean Theorem",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students square right triangles’ side lengths and recognize that the sum of the two shorter sides’ squares equals the longest side’s square. They identify this relationship as the Pythagorean Theorem. Students use cutouts and guided directions to explain proofs of the theorem. They apply the Pythagorean Theorem to solve for the hypotenuse or a leg length of a right triangle with or without context."
  },
